This paper presents a deep learning approach for camera relocalization, which involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) applications. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.RO are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses Bayesian neural networks, which are a popular topic in machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper presents state-of-the-art results on a large-scale outdoor dataset, which is a common focus of the computer vision and pattern recognition (CVPR) community.
